content:
Using a cache to store frequently accessed, infrequently updated Data Mapper and Integration Procedure data saves round trips to the database and improves performance.

Data Mappers use either the Scale Cache or Platform Cache. If you use OmniStudio, Data Mappers use the Scale Cache. If you use OmniStudio for Vlocity, Data Mappers use the Platform Cache. Metadata is automatically cached unless you turn off the Scale Cache.

You can configure data caching on the Options tab of Data Mapper Extracts, Turbo Extracts, and Transforms.

If you call a Data Mapper from an Integration Procedure that uses caching, the Data Mapper data is cached along with the Integration Procedure data.

Integration Procedures use either the Scale Cache or Platform Cache. You can cache metadata for the entire Integration Procedure, cache the response of the entire Integration Procedure, or cache the result of a specific set of steps by placing them inside a Cache Block.

Metadata Cache for Data Mappers and Integration Procedures

Before caching Integration Procedure and Data Mapper metadata in the Platform Cache, allocate space in the VlocityMetadata cache partition. Integration Procedure metadata is cached by default, and Data Mapper metadata is automatically cached.

Methods to Clear Metadata from Either Cache

Clear Data Mapper metadata from the Scale Cache or Platform Cache using one of these lines of code:

* `namespace.DRGlobal.clearCacheForDataRaptor('DataMapperName');`
* `vlocity.cmt.DRGlobal.clearCacheForAllDataRaptor();`

Clear Integration Procedure metadata from the Scale Cache or Platform Cache using this line of code:

* `omnistudio.IntegrationProcedureService.clearMetadataCache('Type_Subtype');`

Clear all cached data for an Integration Procedure using this line of code:

* `omnistudio.IntegrationProcedureService.clearAllCache('Type_Subtype');`

Methods to Clear Data from the Scale Cache

Clear Data Mapper or Integration Procedure data from the Scale Cache using one of these lines of code:

* `namespace.ScaleCacheService.invalidateCacheValue(new Map<String, String>{'DataMapperId' => 'DataMapper_Name'});`
* `namespace.ScaleCacheService.invalidateCacheValue(new Map<String, String>{'VIPId' => Type_SubType});`

Configure Top-Level Caching for an Integration Procedure

To configure top-level caching for an Integration Procedure, go to the Procedure Configuration and set the Salesforce Platform Cache Type and Time To Live In Minutes properties.

Create a Top-Level Caching Example

An Integration Procedure accepts a list of first or last names and retrieves Contacts having those names. Top-level caching to the VlocityAPIResponse partition improves Contact retrieval performance.

Turn Off the Scale Cache

To turn off the Scale Cache, go to Setup and add the TurnOffScaleCache setting to the Omni Interaction Configuration.
title: Omnistudio Caching
